Kiwi
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:proprietary or trade name esp. for a boot polish (? because brown)
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See: -
Pronunciation:
Notes: [HWO writes 1984 to enquirer: I have an idea that <i>Kiwi</i>, the name of its competitor bootpolish, was given to that product in England before the First World War, because it was originally a brown boot polish. It's amusing that <i>nugget</i> should become a well-known word in New Zealand for bootpolish, and <i>Kiwi</i> merely remain the name of a brand here. One might expect that it would have been the other way around.]
