Quote:   in Covent Garden i saw kumeras being sold under that name. `The words `Kiwi' and `Kia-ora' were familiar to everyone partly as trade names for boot-polish and Lemonade [sic]], but also their meanings were generally known. i understand that Kiwi is used in U.S.A. as a name for ground staff at airfields because they don't fly.
